    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Scroll of Stone Shape</strong> (Level 4 Transmutation)</p><p>You touch a stone object of Medium size or smaller or a section of stone no more than 5 feet in any dimension and form it into any shape that suits your purpose. So, for example, you could shape a large rock into a weapon, idol, or coffer, or make a small passage through a wall, as long as the wall is less than 5 feet thick. You could also shape a stone door or its frame to seal the door shut. The object you create can have up to two hinges and a latch, but finer mechanical detail isn't possible.</p><p><strong>Components:</strong> V, S, M (Soft clay, to be crudely worked into the desired shape for the stone object.)</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action | <strong>Range:</strong> Touch | <strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</p><p><em>Classes: Cleric, Druid, Wizard</em></p>",
